{ 8.Nf3  exf4  works out OK for Black. White is now set to capture on e5 and go Bf4 and O-O-O, and also sets a small trap }
8... exf4 9. Bxf4 Bg4 10. a3
{ Kicking the bishop away. Instead,  10.O-O-O!?  Bxc3  11.Nxc3  Bxd1  12.Rxd1  might tempt aggressive types, but it seems that White has no more than some compensation after  12...Nbd7  . }
10... Bxe2 11. axb4 Bxd3 12. cxd3
{ leaves White dominating with his strong centre and pressure down the a- and f-files after O-O. }
