{ as in Miladinovic-Strikovic, Serbian Team Championship 2011 @@StartBracket@@note too famed creative player Igor Miladinovic, of @@StartFEN@@rnbqkbnr/pppppppp/8/8/8/8/PPPPPPPP/RNBQKBNR w KQkq - 0 1@@EndFEN@@  1.d4  Nf6  2.Bg5  Ne4  3.h4!?  fame, playing this line as White@@EndBracket@@, doesn't equalize. }
11. Bf4 c6 12. O-O-O+ Kc7
{ White's play thus far has been quite straightforward, but what to do with no good way to exploit the pin and  13.Bc4  Nfd7!  keeping Black afloat? The answer is to expand on the kingside }
13. h3
{ White may then go Bc4 if Black goes 13...Bd7, but otherwise the plan is Be2 and g4, seizing some very useful space. Black will be able to prevent g5 with ...h6, but then White may well go Rhg1 and h4, with the initiative and advantage. }
