{ White was provoked and  7.d5!?  Ne5  8.Be2  also turned out pretty well in Wolff-T.Wall, London 1985. }
7... e5
{ can, as so often in our earlier coverage, be well met by a simple exchange: }
8. dxe5
{ Black will be undone on b5, d5 or f5 if he allows the queens to come off, but otherwise White will enjoy the easier development and more mobile pawns: }
8... Nxe5 9. Qd2
{ The bishop can go to f4, as well as d4, if attacked and White simply intends O-O-O and f4, full steam ahead! }
