{ Black is quite solid here and may objectively be OK, but White enjoys easy play with Qe2 or Nh3 @@StartBracket@@it's important to prevent a rather awkward check on g5 before housing the king@@EndBracket@@ followed by O-O-O. From f4 his knight may journey on to h5 or even d5 and an advance of Harry could also follow. }
