3. exf5 { Needless to say the proof of the pudding lies in the eating. } 3...
d5 4. Bb5
{ Simple chess @@StartBracket@@4.d4 is also strong@@EndBracket@@, as White is happy to return the extra pawn to exploit the rather large hole Black has kindly created on e5. Instead,  4.Nh4?  is what Black is hoping for when he can go  4...Nh6  or even  4...e5!?  5.Qh5+  g6!  6.fxg6  Nf6  7.g7+  Nxh5  8.gxh8Q  Qxh4  with a right mess. }
