{ This would be a pure Tarrasch if White now went  8.Nbd2  , but instead he can maintain the tension and play for queenside expansion: }
8. a3 c4 9. Bc2 b5
{ is the sort of thing which worries some club players, but after the queen-and-f-pawn-freeing }
