1. e4
{ Not least in our coverage of the Remaining Fianchettoes, we've pretty much looked at all Black's options and will draw the line at the likes of  1...f6  and  1...a5  . Sometimes you just have to enjoy a strong center after  2.d4  and play chess from a position of strength! }
1... e6 2. d4
{ normally leads, of course, to the French, although Black can also enter Owen's waters here. We should mention as well }
2... c5
{ Now  3.d5  leads to quite a pleasant advantage for White and a cramped, inferior version of a Benoni for Black after  3...exd5  4.exd5  d6  5.Nc3  . If you prefer, White can also maintain the tension }
3. c3
{ Black usually responds with  3...d5  when after  4.e5  we're back into the Advance French, as covered in Grandmaster Gambits: 1. e4. Otherwise, White should just enjoy a nice central space advantage: }
3... b6
{ is slightly cheeky, heading for Owen's waters only now, if not a great version for Black: }
4. Nf3 Bb7 5. d5
{ Our favourite retort to ...c5 and one which simply closes down the bishop on b7. Is White's center about to crumble? Well, no: }
5... Nf6 6. Bg5
{ Simple chess, although  6.Qe2!?  with the ideas of c4 and/or e5 might suit creative souls. }
6... h6 7. Bxf6 Qxf6 8. Bc4
{ White has maintained central control, blocked out the bishop on b7 and has a very pleasant edge; ...Ba6 can always be met with Nbd2 or Na3, replacing one good piece on c4 with another one and pawn grabbing will backfire on Black:   8...Qg6  9.Nbd2!  Qxg2?  10.Rg1  Qh3  11.dxe6!  An important exchange and one which spells serious danger for Black on the light squares:  11...dxe6   11...fxe6  12.Ne5  followed by Ng6 or Rg3 Qxh2; Qg4, or if  12...Qxh2  13.Ndf3!  Qf4  14.Rg4  Qf6  15.Bb5!  with a winning attack against the king on e8, as shown by  15...Bc6   or  15...Qd8  16.Qb3  16.Bxc6  dxc6  17.Rg6  Qe7  18.Qb3  and Rxe6.  12.Bb5+!  12...Bc6  13.Bxc6+  Nxc6  14.Qa4  there's just no defense:  14...Rc8  15.Ne5  Qxh2  16.Ndf3  Qf4  17.Rg4!  and the knight on c6 will fall.   12...Nc6  13.Qa4  Rc8  14.Qxa7  is just a game-ender and   12...Kd8  13.Ne5  also rather hopeless for Black. }
