10. dxe5
{ Simple chess; Black's knight will now become a target for the f-pawn. } 10...
Nxe5 11. Qg2
{ We're surprised that White has only scored 80% from this position, which tells you all you need to know. One threat is f4 followed by e5; another f4, Be2 and h4 with a huge kingside pawn roller, for example:   11...Nfd7  12.h4!?  possible now that Black can't really go ...h5 in response  12...Nc6  13.Nd5  there is probably no need to fear ...Bxc3, but centralization is rarely a bad policy  13...Nb6  14.g5!  Nxd5  15.exd5  Ne7  16.Bd3  . This dissuaded ...Nf5 and left h5 followed by Qh3/Qh2 on the way with idyllic attacking chances for White in Grinberg-Bachmann, Internet @@StartBracket@@blitz@@EndBracket@@ 2020. }
