[White "Nimzowitsch G1: 2...d6"]
[Black "G1: 2...d6  #23"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 Nc6 2. Nf3 d6
{ The independent main line of the Nimzowitsch and how Tony Miles always used to meet 2. Nf3. It's also slightly more popular than Black's other common choice at this juncture,  2...e5  . }
3. d4 { Needless to say, White helps himself to the central space on offer. }
3... Bg4
{ pins, but White should be happy to advance and raise Black in the central stakes: }
4. d5 Ne5 5. Nxe5
{ Boom! This queen sacrifice has long been known to significantly favour White: }
5... Bxd1 6. Bb5+ c6 7. dxc6 Qa5+ 8. Nc3 O-O-O 9. Nc4
{ A dream position for White, who enjoys a strong initiative. Thanks to the strong possibility of Nd5 and c7 Black's queen can't really retreat, but even going forwards doesn't especially help him due to some forcing play: }
9... Qb4 10. a3 Qc5 11. Be3 Qh5
{ With all White's pieces on good squares, it's now time to expose the black king: }
12. cxb7+ Kxb7 13. Na5+
{ Wherever the king retreats to, White will recapture on d1, leaving him with two pieces and a pawn for the queen - and especially a huge attack. Just contrast the difference between the number of attackers and defenders on the queenside! One major attacking idea will be Rd1-d4 or Rd5:   13...Ka8  14.Rxd1  e6   14...e5?  15.Bc6+  Kb8  16.Nb5!  when there just isn't a defense due to  16...a6  17.Ba7+  Kc8  18.Rd3!  , and if  18...axb5  19.Rc3  Rd7  20.Bb6!  Rc7  21.Bb7+  . We should probably stop the line here, but it's hard not to enjoy such a dream attacking scenario:  21...Kd7  22.Rxc7+  Ke6  23.Bd5+  Kf6  and now White can do even better than exchange on f7:  24.g4!  , winning the bishop on f8 for starters or simply killing the black king, as with  24...Qg6  25.h4!  Qxg4  26.Rxf7+  Kg6  27.h5+  Kh6  28.Be3+  .  15.Nc6  Rd7  16.Rd4!  White simply wants to go Ra4 and remove the a-pawn, and even challenging the knight on c6 doesn't especially help Black:  16...Ne7  17.Rb4!  followed by Be2 or  17...Qxb5  18.Nxb5  Nxc6  19.Rc4  with a clear extra pawn and ongoing initiative. }
