{ is a very pleasant edge for White. Rg1 will increase the pressure against g7 and White simply wants to go Be3 and O-O-O, after which Qc4 or Qa4 might prove rather awkward with ...Qd7 running into e5, exploiting the line-up of queen and opposing rook on the d-file. }
*

